SYNTHETIC — NOT A REAL CASE

To Mr. Whitlock and to supervisor escalation:

The salvage transfer of the 1969 Mustang Mach 1 yesterday was not
authorized by me. I have never signed a release. My written objection
of 2025-05-22 remains on the record and was not withdrawn.

Under CIM-SALV-2023 §3, salvage transfer requires either (a) a
completed total-loss settlement with signed release from the insured
or (b) written consent to proceed before settlement. Neither occurred.

I require the following in writing within 5 business days:

 1. An explanation of under what clause you believe the transfer was
    authorized.
 2. A commitment that the settlement check, if issued, is not
    construed as constructive acceptance of the offer.
 3. Either return of the vehicle or payment of the full agreed value
    ($58,000) less the $500 deductible.

I will file a complaint with the Maryland Insurance Administration if
this is not resolved within 30 days.

— Delia Vance
